-- Tamil Nadu Newsprint to Import 300,000 Tons of Non-Coking Coal
-- B y   A r c h a n a   C h a u d h a r y
-- 2012-09-06T07:21:24Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-09-06/tamil-nadu-newsprint-to-import-300-000-tons-of-non-coking-coal.html
Tamil Nadu Newsprint & Papers Ltd. (TNNP) ,
an Indian paper maker, is seeking 300,000 metric tons of non-
coking coal starting November this year.  The Chennai-based company has sought delivery of fuel
imported from Indonesia, Australia,  South Africa  or China in six
shipments of about 50,000 tons each at its Pugalur factory,
according to the companyâ€™s tender  document .  The company has sought coal with a gross calorific value of
6,000 kilocalories a kilogram, total moisture around 15 percent,
ash content of maximum 8 percent and sulfur content not more
than 0.8 percent. The last date of submission of bids is Sept.
20, according to the company.  To contact the reporter on this story:
